  "prompt": "The best YouTube to learn Spanish?",
  "response": "There are many excellent YouTube channels for learning Spanish, catering to different levels and learning styles. Here are some of the best:\n\n---\n\n### **1. SpanishPod101**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Offers structured lessons for all levels, from beginner to advanced. Focuses on vocabulary, grammar, and cultural insights.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want a systematic approach.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Butterfly Spanish**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Ana, the teacher, explains grammar and pronunciation in a clear and engaging way. Her lessons are fun and easy to follow.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want to focus on grammar and speaking.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Dreaming Spanish**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Uses the comprehensible input method, where you learn by listening to stories and conversations. Great for improving listening skills and picking up vocabulary naturally.\n- **Good for:** All levels, especially if you want to improve listening and comprehension.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Hola Spanish**\n- **PhWhy it\u2019s great:** Brenda teaches practical Spanish with lessons on everyday phrases, slang, and culture. Her videos are lively and interactive.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want to learn conversational Spanish.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Easy Spanish**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Features real-life conversations with subtitles in Spanish and English. Helps you learn how native speakers talk in everyday situations.\n- **Good for:** Intermediate and advanced learners who want to improve listening and conversational skills.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Why Not Spanish?**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Focuses on practical language skills and cultural insights. Offers challenges and exercises to practice what you\u2019ve learned.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want a mix of grammar and conversation practice.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Spanish with Vicente**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Excellent for advanced learners. Focuses on grammar nuances, advanced vocabulary, and preparing for exams like DELE.\n- **Good for:** Advanced learners and those preparing for proficiency tests.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Se\u00f1or Jordan / Profesor Jason**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Both channels focus on grammar and vocabulary with clear explanations and examples. Great for structured learning.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want to focus on grammar.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Learn Spanish with Paulino**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Simple and effective lessons that focus on vocabulary and phrases. Perfect for beginners.\n- **Good for:** Absolute beginners.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Chill Spanish Listening**\n- **Why it\u2019s great:** Relaxing, slow-paced lessons that focus on listening and comprehension. Great for casual learning.\n- **Good for:** Beginners and intermediate learners who want to improve listening skills.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Choosing:\n- **Beginners:** Start with Butterfly Spanish, SpanishPod101, or Dreaming Spanish.\n- **Intermediate:** Try Hola Spanish, Easy Spanish, or Why Not Spanish?\n- **Advanced:** Go for Spanish with Vicente or Easy Spanish for authentic conversations.\n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like more tailored recommendations! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
